HEADWORD: Kairoline
<hw>Kai`ro*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>An organic base obtained from quinoline. It is used as a febrifuge,
and resembles kairine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

